  Schema: Condition_evaluation_arm
   <express_ref linkend="condition_evaluation:arm:Condition_evaluation_arm"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Condition_evaluation_arm">The condition evaluation ARM provides the construct to record the evaluation values of the criteria parameters, the criteria instances and the condition. It also provides a reference to the object for which the condition is evaluated. 
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Condition_evaluation_arm  Entity: Condition_evaluation  
   <express_ref linkend="condition_evaluation:arm:Condition_evaluation_arm.Condition_evaluation"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Condition_evaluation_arm.Condition_assertion">
        A <b>Condition_assertion</b> is a  record of the result of evaluating a condition. The assertion of a condition conclusion is based on the result of the relevant collector criterion.
<note>For conditions defined by criterion parameters, there is always a top level criterion that collects the total result of the involved parameters through appropriate logical operators.
</note>
      </ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Condition_evaluation_arm  Entity: Condition_evaluation  Attribute: assertion 
   <express_ref linkend="condition_evaluation:arm:Condition_evaluation_arm.Condition_evaluation.assertion"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Condition_evaluation_arm.Condition_assertion.assertion">
          the result of evaluating the condition.
        </ext_description>
